---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Multidimensional Ideological Model"
  description="Explore 20 political ideologies in continuous 3D space, animated across 400 years of history."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section style="min-height:100vh;display:flex;flex-direction:column;justify-content:center;align-items:center;text-align:center;padding:6rem 1.5rem;position:relative;overflow:hidden;">
    <!-- Background glow -->
    <div style="position:absolute;inset:0;pointer-events:none;overflow:hidden;">
      <div style="position:absolute;top:20%;left:50%;transform:translate(-50%,-50%);width:600px;height:600px;border-radius:50%;background:radial-gradient(circle,rgba(129,140,248,0.07) 0%,transparent 70%);"></div>
      <div style="position:absolute;top:50%;left:30%;width:300px;height:300px;border-radius:50%;background:radial-gradient(circle,rgba(239,68,68,0.05) 0%,transparent 70%);"></div>
      <div style="position:absolute;top:40%;right:25%;width:250px;height:250px;border-radius:50%;background:radial-gradient(circle,rgba(34,197,94,0.04) 0%,transparent 70%);"></div>
    </div>

    <!-- Badge -->
    <div style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:0.5rem;padding:0.375rem 1rem;border-radius:9999px;border:1px solid var(--color-border);background:var(--color-surface);font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--color-muted);margin-bottom:2rem;">
      <span style="width:6px;height:6px;border-radius:50%;background:var(--color-axis-y);"></span>
      Open Source · Academic Research Tool
    </div>

    <!-- Sphere icon -->
    <div style="position:relative;width:96px;height:96px;margin:0 auto 2rem;">
      <div style="width:96px;height:96px;border-radius:50%;background:conic-gradient(from 0deg,#ef4444,#f97316,#22c55e,#3b82f6,#818cf8,#ef4444);opacity:0.85;filter:blur(2px);"></div>
      <div style="position:absolute;inset:6px;border-radius:50%;border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.15);background:rgba(7,7,16,0.3);"></div>
      <!-- Axis lines -->
      <div style="position:absolute;inset:0;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;">
        <div style="width:100%;height:1px;background:rgba(239,68,68,0.6);"></div>
      </div>
      <div style="position:absolute;inset:0;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;">
        <div style="width:1px;height:100%;background:rgba(34,197,94,0.6);"></div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Title -->
    <h1 class="hero-title">
      Multidimensional<br>
      <span style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#818cf8,#c084fc,#818cf8);-webkit-background-clip:text;-webkit-text-fill-color:transparent;background-clip:text;">Ideological Model</span>
    </h1>

    <!-- Subtitle -->
    <p style="font-size:clamp(1rem,2.5vw,1.25rem);color:var(--color-muted);max-width:560px;line-height:1.65;margin:0 0 3rem;">
      Explore 20 political ideologies as vectors in continuous 3D space — animated across
      <strong style="color:var(--color-text);">400 years of history</strong> and shaped by gravitational historical forces.
    </p>

    <!-- CTAs -->
    <div style="display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:1rem;justify-content:center;">
      <a href="/quiz" style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:0.5rem;padding:0.875rem 2rem;border-radius:0.75rem;background:var(--color-accent);color:#fff;font-weight:600;font-size:1rem;text-decoration:none;transition:opacity 0.15s;">
        Find My Position →
      </a>
      <a href="/tool" style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:0.5rem;padding:0.875rem 2rem;border-radius:0.75rem;border:1px solid var(--color-border);background:var(--color-surface);color:var(--color-text);font-weight:500;font-size:1rem;text-decoration:none;transition:background 0.15s;">
        Open Tool Directly
      </a>
    </div>

    <!-- Scroll hint -->
    <div style="position:absolute;bottom:2.5rem;left:50%;transform:translateX(-50%);color:var(--color-muted);font-size:0.75rem;display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:center;gap:0.5rem;">
      <span>Scroll to learn more</span>
      <span style="animation:bounce 1.5s infinite;">↓</span>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Three Axes -->
  <section style="padding:6rem 1.5rem;max-width:1100px;margin:0 auto;">
    <div style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:3.5rem;">
      <h2 style="font-size:2rem;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:-0.02em;margin:0 0 0.75rem;">Three Dimensions of Ideology</h2>
      <p style="color:var(--color-muted);font-size:1rem;max-width:520px;margin:0 auto;">
        Unlike traditional 1D left-right spectrums or 2D political compasses,
        this model captures ideology along three independent axes.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(280px,1fr));gap:1.5rem;">
      <!-- X Axis -->
      <div style="background:var(--color-card);border:1px solid var(--color-border);border-left:3px solid var(--color-axis-x);border-radius:0.875rem;padding:1.75rem;">
        <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:0.75rem;margin-bottom:1rem;">
          <div style="width:36px;height:36px;border-radius:0.5rem;background:rgba(239,68,68,0.12);display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;font-weight:700;font-size:0.9rem;color:var(--color-axis-x);">X</div>
          <div>
            <div style="font-weight:600;font-size:1rem;">Economic Axis</div>
            <div style="font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--color-muted);">Range: −1.0 to +1.0</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div style="display:flex;justify-content:space-between;font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--color-muted);margin-bottom:0.5rem;">
          <span>← Collective / Left</span>
          <span>Right / Individual →</span>
        </div>
        <div style="height:3px;border-radius:9999px;background:linear-gradient(to right,#ef4444,rgba(239,68,68,0.15));margin-bottom:1rem;"></div>
        <p style="font-size:0.875rem;color:var(--color-muted);line-height:1.6;margin:0;">
          How should resources, production, and wealth be organized?
          From collective ownership and redistribution on the left,
          to private property and free markets on the right.
        </p>
        <div style="margin-top:1rem;font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--color-border);border-top:1px solid var(--color-border);padding-top:0.75rem;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;">
          <span style="color:var(--color-axis-x);opacity:0.7;">−1: Anarchism, Stalinism</span>
          <span style="color:var(--color-axis-x);opacity:0.7;">+1: Anarcho-Capitalism</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Y Axis -->
      <div style="background:var(--color-card);border:1px solid var(--color-border);border-left:3px solid var(--color-axis-y);border-radius:0.875rem;padding:1.75rem;">
        <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:0.75rem;margin-bottom:1rem;">
          <div style="width:36px;height:36px;border-radius:0.5rem;background:rgba(34,197,94,0.1);display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;font-weight:700;font-size:0.9rem;color:var(--color-axis-y);">Y</div>
          <div>
            <div style="font-weight:600;font-size:1rem;">Authority Axis</div>
            <div style="font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--color-muted);">Range: −1.0 to +1.0</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div style="display:flex;justify-content:space-between;font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--color-muted);margin-bottom:0.5rem;">
          <span>← Libertarian / Free</span>
          <span>Authoritarian / Order →</span>
        </div>
        <div style="height:3px;border-radius:9999px;background:linear-gradient(to right,#22c55e,rgba(34,197,94,0.15));margin-bottom:1rem;"></div>
        <p style="font-size:0.875rem;color:var(--color-muted);line-height:1.6;margin:0;">
          How much authority should the state exercise over individuals?
          From maximum personal freedom and minimal governance,
          to strong central control and enforced social order.
        </p>
        <div style="margin-top:1rem;font-size:0.75rem;border-top:1px solid var(--color-border);padding-top:0.75rem;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;">
          <span style="color:var(--color-axis-y);opacity:0.7;">−1: Anarchism, Libertarianism</span>
          <span style="color:var(--color-axis-y);opacity:0.7;">+1: Fascism, Theocracy</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Z Axis -->
      <div style="background:var(--color-card);border:1px solid var(--color-border);border-left:3px solid var(--color-axis-z);border-radius:0.875rem;padding:1.75rem;">
        <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:0.75rem;margin-bottom:1rem;">
          <div style="width:36px;height:36px;border-radius:0.5rem;background:rgba(59,130,246,0.1);display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;font-weight:700;font-size:0.9rem;color:var(--color-axis-z);">Z</div>
          <div>
            <div style="font-weight:600;font-size:1rem;">Identity Axis</div>
            <div style="font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--color-muted);">Range: −1.0 to +1.0</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div style="display:flex;justify-content:space-between;font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--color-muted);margin-bottom:0.5rem;">
          <span>← Cosmopolitan / Progressive</span>
          <span>Nationalist / Traditional →</span>
        </div>
        <div style="height:3px;border-radius:9999px;background:linear-gradient(to right,#3b82f6,rgba(59,130,246,0.15));margin-bottom:1rem;"></div>
        <p style="font-size:0.875rem;color:var(--color-muted);line-height:1.6;margin:0;">
          How should societies relate to national identity and culture?
          From open borders, globalism, and cultural pluralism,
          to national sovereignty, heritage, and cultural preservation.
        </p>
        <div style="margin-top:1rem;font-size:0.75rem;border-top:1px solid var(--color-border);padding-top:0.75rem;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;">
          <span style="color:var(--color-axis-z);opacity:0.7;">−1: Eco-Socialism, Anarchism</span>
          <span style="color:var(--color-axis-z);opacity:0.7;">+1: Nationalism, Fascism</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Why Multidimensional -->
  <section style="padding:5rem 1.5rem;border-top:1px solid var(--color-border);">
    <div class="why-2d-grid">
      <div>
        <h2 style="font-size:1.75rem;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:-0.02em;margin:0 0 1rem;">Why not just 2D?</h2>
        <p style="color:var(--color-muted);line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 1rem;">
          The traditional <em>Political Compass</em> maps ideologies onto two axes — economic and social.
          While intuitive, academia has long criticized this as insufficient:
          it collapses distinct phenomena (nationalism, cultural values, identity) into a single axis.
        </p>
        <p style="color:var(--color-muted);line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 1.5rem;">
          Research published in <em>Nature Human Behaviour</em> (2025), <em>Applied Network Science</em> (2023),
          and at NAACL (2022) independently corroborates the need for multidimensional models.
          Our model adds a dedicated <strong style="color:var(--color-text);">Identity axis</strong>
          to capture the nationalism-cosmopolitanism dimension that defines much of 21st-century politics.
        </p>
        <a href="/about#model" style="color:var(--color-accent);font-size:0.875rem;text-decoration:none;">Read more about the model →</a>
      </div>
      <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:0.75rem;">
        <div style="background:var(--color-card);border:1px solid var(--color-border);border-radius:0.75rem;padding:1.25rem;">
          <div style="font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--color-muted);margin-bottom:0.25rem;">1D Model</div>
          <div style="font-weight:500;">Left ←——→ Right</div>
          <div style="font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--color-muted);margin-top:0.25rem;">Cannot distinguish Fascism from Conservatism or Anarchism from Social Democracy.</div>
        </div>
        <div style="background:var(--color-card);border:1px solid var(--color-border);border-radius:0.75rem;padding:1.25rem;">
          <div style="font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--color-muted);margin-bottom:0.25rem;">2D Model (Political Compass)</div>
          <div style="font-weight:500;">Economic × Social/Authority</div>
          <div style="font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--color-muted);margin-top:0.25rem;">Better — but conflates identity, nationalism, and cultural values into one axis.</div>
        </div>
        <div style="background:var(--color-card);border:1px solid var(--color-accent-dim);border-radius:0.75rem;padding:1.25rem;">
          <div style="font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--color-accent);margin-bottom:0.25rem;">3D Model (This Tool)</div>
          <div style="font-weight:500;">Economic × Authority × Identity</div>
          <div style="font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--color-muted);margin-top:0.25rem;">Separates the three core dimensions of political thought with independent precision.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Features -->
  <section style="padding:5rem 1.5rem;max-width:1100px;margin:0 auto;">
    <h2 style="font-size:1.75rem;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:-0.02em;text-align:center;margin:0 0 3rem;">What you can explore</h2>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(200px,1fr));gap:1.5rem;">
      {[
        { icon: '🌐', title: '20 Ideologies', desc: 'From Classical Liberalism to Maoism, Fascism to Municipalism — positioned with mathematical precision.' },
        { icon: '⏱️', title: '400 Years', desc: 'Animate from the French Revolution (1789) to the present. Watch ideologies emerge and shift.' },
        { icon: '🌌', title: 'Historical Gravity', desc: 'Major events (1917, 1933, 1989) act as gravitational forces pulling ideologies through ideological space.' },
        { icon: '📍', title: 'Your Position', desc: 'Place yourself in the model via the quiz or manual sliders. See which ideology you are closest to.' },
        { icon: '🔵', title: 'Live Clustering', desc: 'K-means clustering reveals ideological groupings as they evolve through history in real time.' },
        { icon: '🎓', title: 'Academic Base', desc: 'Grounded in sociophysics, political science literature, and formal mathematical formalization.' },
      ].map(f => (
        <div style="background:var(--color-card);border:1px solid var(--color-border);border-radius:0.75rem;padding:1.5rem;">
          <div style="font-size:1.5rem;margin-bottom:0.75rem;">{f.icon}</div>
          <div style="font-weight:600;margin-bottom:0.5rem;">{f.title}</div>
          <div style="font-size:0.875rem;color:var(--color-muted);line-height:1.6;">{f.desc}</div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How to Use -->
  <section style="padding:5rem 1.5rem;border-top:1px solid var(--color-border);">
    <div style="max-width:700px;margin:0 auto;text-align:center;">
      <h2 style="font-size:1.75rem;font-weight:700;margin:0 0 0.75rem;">How to use it</h2>
      <p style="color:var(--color-muted);margin:0 0 3rem;">Two paths, same destination — your place in ideological space.</p>

      <div class="paths-grid">
        <div style="background:var(--color-card);border:1px solid var(--color-border);border-radius:0.875rem;padding:1.75rem;">
          <div style="font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--color-accent);font-weight:600;letter-spacing:0.05em;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:1rem;">Path A — Quiz</div>
          <ol style="color:var(--color-muted);font-size:0.875rem;line-height:1.8;padding-left:1.25rem;margin:0 0 1.5rem;">
            <li>Answer 15 political questions</li>
            <li>Get your position calculated automatically</li>
            <li>Land directly in the 3D model</li>
          </ol>
          <a href="/quiz" style="display:inline-block;padding:0.625rem 1.25rem;border-radius:0.5rem;background:var(--color-accent);color:#fff;font-weight:600;font-size:0.875rem;text-decoration:none;">Take Quiz →</a>
        </div>
        <div style="background:var(--color-card);border:1px solid var(--color-border);border-radius:0.875rem;padding:1.75rem;">
          <div style="font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--color-muted);font-weight:600;letter-spacing:0.05em;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:1rem;">Path B — Explore</div>
          <ol style="color:var(--color-muted);font-size:0.875rem;line-height:1.8;padding-left:1.25rem;margin:0 0 1.5rem;">
            <li>Open the 3D tool directly</li>
            <li>Set X, Y, Z sliders manually</li>
            <li>Drag to rotate, scroll to zoom</li>
          </ol>
          <a href="/tool" style="display:inline-block;padding:0.625rem 1.25rem;border-radius:0.5rem;border:1px solid var(--color-border);background:var(--color-surface);color:var(--color-text);font-weight:500;font-size:0.875rem;text-decoration:none;">Open Tool</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p style="margin-top:2rem;font-size:0.8rem;color:var(--color-muted);">
        In the tool: drag to rotate · scroll to zoom · ← → ↑ ↓ keys to navigate · + / − to zoom
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Bottom CTA -->
  <section style="padding:6rem 1.5rem;text-align:center;border-top:1px solid var(--color-border);">
    <h2 style="font-size:2rem;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:-0.02em;margin:0 0 1rem;">Where do you stand?</h2>
    <p style="color:var(--color-muted);font-size:1.05rem;max-width:480px;margin:0 auto 2rem;">
      Take the 5-minute positioning quiz and see yourself in the ideological landscape.
    </p>
    <a href="/quiz" style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:0.5rem;padding:1rem 2.5rem;border-radius:0.75rem;background:var(--color-accent);color:#fff;font-weight:600;font-size:1.05rem;text-decoration:none;">
      Start the Quiz →
    </a>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  @keyframes bounce {
    0%, 100% { transform: translateY(0); }
    50% { transform: translateY(6px); }
  }

  .hero-title {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 6vw, 4.5rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    line-height: 1.05;
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
    max-width: 800px;
  }

  .why-2d-grid {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 4rem;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .paths-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    text-align: left;
  }

  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .hero-title {
      font-size: 1.75rem;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 699px) {
    .why-2d-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 2rem;
    }

    .paths-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
